  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Deepening Decentralization Programme (DDP): In order to reduce poverty, promote inclusive economic growth and entrench democratic principles through improved decentralization, the government of Lesotho through the Ministry of Local Government and Chieftainship has in partnership with European Union (EU), United Nations Capital Development Fund (UNCDF) and United Nations Development Programme (UNDP) designed the Deepening Decentralization Project (DDP). Building on the previous collaborative work of the government of Lesotho and these partners in the area of decentralization, this project aims to accelerate progress and deepen decentralization in Lesotho. The main purpose is to promote decentralized service delivery for social and economic growth through the development of transparent funding mechanisms and by improving the accountability of local authorities.</narrative>
  </description>
